      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEAR NOT FRANKY (1) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at this track over 318m behind Total Temptation (18.97) in a Grade 5. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Worth another chance. RAY OF EVE (8) failed to come into contention last start at Wagga, but prior to that won comfortably by 5 lengths at Wagga (18.31) beating Winning Hand in a Grade 5 on May 15. Worth following up. TOMMY TARO (2) was on speed settling but found some traffic when checked, missing the frame to finish seventh (26.03) at Gunnedah in a Grade 5. Safe beginner and drawn well close to the inside. Key player if finds best. SKYLIFT (4) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
